Female:
tergum VIII as wide as long; posterior margin truncate (
Fig. 51
). Sternum VIII as wide as long; posterior margin broadly rounded, somewhat truncate at the middle, with short setae restricted to posterior margin (
Fig. 52
). Tergum IX with very short and symmetrical ventral struts. Tergum X with anterior margin somewhat truncate and posterior margin very slightly emarginated at the middle (
Fig. 53
). Spermatheca long, somewhat L-shaped; capsule of spermatheca long and without apical invagination, or it is very short and difficult see (
Fig. 54
).

